# **Industrial Training Report**

## **Day 01**

**Company:** Pixxelu, Dharamshala
**Training Duration:** 4 Weeks
**Training Domain:** HTML, CSS & CMS (WordPress)

---

## **Objective**

The objective of today's training was to learn the basics of HTML and understand how a simple web page is created. We also learned how different HTML tags are used to organize and display content on a webpage.

---

## **Topics Covered**

* Introduction to HTML
* Basic Structure of an HTML Document
* HTML Boilerplate
* Heading Tags (`<h1>` to `<h6>`)
* Paragraph and Text Formatting Tags
* Semantic and Non-Semantic Tags
* Inline and Block Elements
* Subscript and Superscript
* Hyperlinks
* Images
* Audio, Video and Iframe
* Ordered, Unordered and Description Lists

---

## **Work Done**

During today's session, I created simple HTML pages and practiced each topic. I learned how to write the basic HTML structure, use different tags, add text formatting, insert images and links, and create lists. I also practiced adding audio, video, and iframe elements to a webpage.

---

## **Learning Outcome**

* Understood the basic structure of an HTML document.
* Learned the purpose of commonly used HTML tags.
* Understood the difference between semantic and non-semantic tags.
* Learned how to create hyperlinks and add images to a webpage.
* Practiced using multimedia elements.
* Gained confidence in creating basic web pages using HTML.

---

## **Conclusion**

The first day of training gave me a good understanding of HTML fundamentals. The practical practice helped me understand how web pages are built, which will be useful for learning CSS and CMS in the coming days.

